project.project_abstract:
The NaCRRI's Rice Breeding program integrates the TRICOT approach in late-stage rice breeding. Chiefly, this will improve the statistical efficiency of end-users' preference data to support various releases/ licensing. Therefore, the piloting implementation of the approach will involve evaluation of uncooked rice and organoleptic testing of cooked rice. For comparison purposes, the team will also evaluate the rice products using the conventional PVS approach with aim of determining the efficacy of the two approaches in late-stage breeding. Overall, the two-fold evaluation will provide recommendations on the optimal approach for participatory selection of advanced rice lines.

During the exercise, the team will evaluate five rice lines ; 3 new lines (K38, K39 and WDR) and 2 checks (Wita 9 and Kaiso). The latter three are earmarked to be released or licensed as official varieties shortly. The locations for the evaluation include NaCRRI (Namulonge), Doho irrigation scheme and Lira irrigation scheme.
